{{Infobox Korean name | hangul = 박윤선 | hanja = 朴允善 | rr = Bak Yun-seon | mr = Pak Yun-sŏn | context = | img = 박윤선박사1967(YSP AMJ).jpg | caption = Dr. Park Yun-sun }}
[[File:YungSun Park(AMJ).jpg|thumb|150px|Professor Park Yun-Sun]] [[File:박윤선성경(AMJ).jpg|thumb|150px|The Bible Commentary of Par Yun-Sun(박윤선박사의 주석성경)]] [[File:박윤선박사 철학사개요(AMJ).jpg|thumb|150px|Lecture Syllabus of Dr. Yun-Sun Park, Korea Theological Seminary, Busan, South Korea, around 1957]] '''Park Yun-Sun''' (December 11, 1905 - June 30, 1988) was a [[Korea]]n [[biblical scholar]] born in [[Cholsan County|Cholsan]], [[North Pyongan Province]]. After completing his undergraduate studies at [[Soongsil University]], he enrolled at [[Westminster Theological Seminary]] in the US. Then, he went on to [[Netherlands|Holland]] for further theological training (October 1953 - March 1954). In 1979, he completed his voluminous and historic scholarly work on the commentaries of all sixty-six books of the [[Old Testament|Old]] and [[New Testament]]s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yunesunpark.pe.kr/|work=yunesunpark.pe.kr/|title=Yune Sun Park Official Site|accessdate=6 April 2011|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120322101346/http://www.yunesunpark.pe.kr/|archivedate=22 March 2012|df=}}</ref> Park has been considered to be the pre-eminent [[John Calvin|Calvin]] scholar in [[Korea]]. He taught at [[Kosin University]] (1946–1960), [[Chongshin University]] (1963–1974, 1979–1980), and [[Hapdong Theological Seminary]] (1980–1988). <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hapdong.ac.kr/outline_history.htm|work=hapdong.ac.kr |title=Hapdong Seminary Official Site}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.reformiert-online.net/adressen/detail.php?id=13119&lg=eng|work=reformiert-online.net |title=Reformiert Online}}</ref> He introduced to Koreans the works of [[Charles Hodge|C. Hodge]], [[John Gresham Machen|Machen]], [[B. B. Warfield|Warfield]], [[Abraham Kuyper|A. Kuyper]], [[Herman Bavinck|Bavinck]], [[Klaas Schilder|Schilder]], and [[Seakle Greijdanus|Greijdanus]].
